{"type":"message","id":"1e19bacb","parentId":"eb70247a","timestamp":"2026-03-25T23:28:29.121Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_LQ76uDs4DF8xpCy1YhZlFw3x|fc_0fc121c358a0b3df0169c46f9f45cc8191b0e1b389c92be7c1","name":"memory_search","arguments":{"query":"Prometeo Claude Code Atlas cambiar entre OpenAI y Claude modelo routing policy preferences Prometeo","maxResults":10},"partialJson":"{\"query\":\"Prometeo Claude Code Atlas cambiar entre OpenAI y Claude modelo routing policy preferences Prometeo\", \"maxResults\":10}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8kBwfuUEuaubmadL3hl006x3|fc_0fc121c358a0b3df0169c46f9f45e08191b855ad2d0d29212a","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/Gustavo/.openclaw/workspace/model-routing-policy.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:/Users/Gustavo/.openclaw/workspace/model-routing-policy.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_DWwjE9g4HkonUFXfQDeap7L7|fc_0fc121c358a0b3df0169c46f9f45e88191aae9407ae2f32ee7","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/Gustavo/AppData/Roaming/npm/node_modules/openclaw/docs/README.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:/Users/Gustavo/AppData/Roaming/npm/node_modules/openclaw/docs/README.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":281,"output":119,"cacheRead":14720,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15120,"cost":{"input":0.0007025000000000001,"output":0.0017850000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0036799999999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.006167499999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774481305892,"responseId":"resp_0fc121c358a0b3df0169c46f9c8c088191a586f80ae7f53304"}}
{"type":"message","id":"164ccbbd","parentId":"1e19bacb","timestamp":"2026-03-25T23:28:29.373Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_LQ76uDs4DF8xpCy1YhZlFw3x|fc_0fc121c358a0b3df0169c46f9f45cc8191b0e1b389c92be7c1","toolName":"memory_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"results\": [],\n  \"provider\": \"none\",\n  \"citations\": \"auto\",\n  \"mode\": \"fts-only\"\n}"}],"details":{"results":[],"provider":"none","citations":"auto","mode":"fts-only"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774481309340}}
{"type":"message","id":"3b24c899","parentId":"164ccbbd","timestamp":"2026-03-25T23:28:29.415Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_8kBwfuUEuaubmadL3hl006x3|fc_0fc121c358a0b3df0169c46f9f45e08191b855ad2d0d29212a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# System routing\n\nAtlas is the router.\n\n## Goal\n\nMaximize quality per token.\nUse the cheapest model that can safely complete the task.\nPreserve strong models for high-value work.\n\n## Priority order\n\n1. ChatGPT (default daily)\n2. Claude Code (coding + hard tasks)\n3. Ollama (fallback / low cost / offline)\n\n## ChatGPT definition\n\nChatGPT is the default reasoning layer and primary daily model.\n\nUse ChatGPT for:\n- planning\n- architecture decisions\n- debugging strategy\n- analysis\n- problem framing\n- prompt design\n- reducing ambiguity\n- second opinions\n\nChatGPT should prioritize:\n- clarity\n- structure\n- concise reasoning\n- actionable outputs\n\n## Claude Code definition\n\nClaude Code is the primary builder.\n\nUse Claude Code when:\n- writing or modifying code\n- implementing features\n- fixing bugs\n- refactoring\n- working with repositories\n- creating scripts or tests\n- executing technical tasks\n- solving complex engineering problems\n\nClaude Code should prioritize:\n- direct execution\n- minimal explanation\n- patch-style outputs\n- fast implementation\n\nRule:\nIf the task requires \"doing\", use Claude Code.\n\n## ChatGPT escalation\n\nUse stronger ChatGPT reasoning when:\n- the problem is complex\n- the task is high-risk\n- architecture decisions have impact\n- debugging is unclear or non-trivial\n\n## Ollama definition (fallback layer)\n\nUse Ollama when:\n- tasks are simple or repetitive\n- preprocessing or formatting is needed\n- summarization is low-risk\n- cloud models are unavailable\n- token budget is limited\n\nDo NOT use Ollama for critical decisions if stronger models are available.\n\n## Ollama roles\n\n### llama3.2:3b\nUse for:\n- ultra-light summaries\n- classification\n- extraction\n- text cleanup\n- trivial tasks\n\n### qwen3:8b\nUse for:\n- rewriting\n- formatting\n- JSON cleanup\n- structured transformations\n- simple coding help\n- low-risk technical explanations\n\n### qwen3:30b\nUse for:\n- fallback reasoning\n- medium/high complexity local analysis\n- coding help without cloud\n- token exhaustion scenarios\n\n## Routing rules\n\n- If the task is reasoning-heavy → use ChatGPT\n- If the task is coding or execution → use Claude Code\n- If the task is complex or critical → escalate to stronger ChatGPT\n- If the task is simple or low-value → use Ollama\n- If cloud is unavailable → use qwen3:30b\n- If tokens are limited → prefer Ollama (qwen3:8b → qwen3:30b)\n\n## Token preservation rules\n\n- Default to concise responses\n- Avoid repeating context\n- Prefer summaries over long explanations\n- Use diffs/patches instead of full rewrites\n- Escalate only when necessary\n- Preserve strong model usage for high-value tasks\n\n## Decision shortcut\n\n- Low effort + low risk → llama3.2:3b\n- Medium effort + low risk → qwen3:8b\n- No cloud / fallback → qwen3:30b\n- Coding → Claude Code\n- Thinking / planning → ChatGPT\n- Complex / critical → stronger ChatGPT\n\n## Output rule\n\nAlways state the selected model in one short line:\n\n`Model: <model_name>`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774481309411}}
{"type":"message","id":"ce6c9f30","parentId":"3b24c899","timestamp":"2026-03-25T23:28:29.419Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_DWwjE9g4HkonUFXfQDeap7L7|fc_0fc121c358a0b3df0169c46f9f45e88191aae9407ae2f32ee7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"read\",\n  \"error\": \"ENOENT: no such file or directory, access 'C:\\\\Users\\\\Gustavo\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\docs\\\\README.md'\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"read","error":"ENOENT: no such file or directory, access 'C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\README.md'"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774481309415}}
{"type":"message","id":"cc8b7add","parentId":"ce6c9f30","timestamp":"2026-03-25T23:28:44.921Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Sí. Y además **cuadra perfecto** con la política que ya definiste:\n\n- **Prometeo → Claude Code** como builder por defecto\n- **Atlas → poder moverse entre OpenAI y Claude según necesidad**\n- **Ollama** queda como capa barata/local, no como única opción\n\nLa idea correcta es esta:\n\n**Prometeo**\n- Déjalo orientado a **Claude Code**\n- Especialmente porque su trabajo es **TradeLab / implementación / repo / ejecución**\n- Eso ya coincide con tu policy: *“If the task requires doing, use Claude Code”*\n\n**Atlas**\n- Debe ser el **router**\n- Puede usar:\n  - **OpenAI/ChatGPT** para pensar, planear, analizar, decidir\n  - **Claude Code** para ejecutar código o trabajo técnico pesado\n  - **Ollama** para barato/local/simple\n\nEl punto clave:\n**que no lo veas en el selector no significa que no se pueda usar**.\nMuchas veces hay que configurar **Claude Code como harness/agente**, no como simple “modelo del dropdown”.\n\nTe lo separo en lo que quieres lograr:\n\n### Lo que quieres\n1. **Prometeo** con acceso a **Claude Code**\n2. **Atlas** con posibilidad de usar **OpenAI o Claude** según el caso\n3. No quedar atrapado viendo **solo Ollama**\n\n### Lo más probable que pasa ahora\n- El **chat UI** solo te está mostrando los modelos del provider actual\n- **Claude Code** no está expuesto en esa vista como modelo seleccionable\n- O todavía **no está configurado** como harness/provider usable por OpenClaw\n\n### Cómo debería quedar conceptualmente\n- **Atlas (main)**:\n  - default: **OpenAI**\n  - cuando toque código/implementación: **Claude Code**\n- **Prometeo**:\n  - default operativo: **Claude Code**\n- **Ollama**:\n  - fallback/local/low-cost\n\n### Importante\nHay dos formas de lograrlo:\n\n**A. Cambio de modelo en sesión**\n- que Atlas pueda cambiar el modelo del chat actual entre providers\n\n**B. Delegación por harness**\n- que Atlas siga en su modelo normal\n- y cuando haga falta mande el trabajo a **Claude Code** (por ejemplo vía ACP/session spawn)\n\nEn OpenClaw, muchas veces **B es la forma más limpia y realista**.\n\n### Mi recomendación\nHazlo así:\n\n- **Atlas**: OpenAI como thinker por defecto\n- **Prometeo**: Claude Code como builder por defecto\n- **Atlas** delega o cambia según tarea, no todo por selector visual\n\nSi quieres, el siguiente paso útil es que te deje un **plan exacto de configuración** para:\n- registrar **Claude Code**\n- asignárselo a **Prometeo**\n- y dejar a **Atlas** con libertad para usar **OpenAI o Claude**\n\nSi quieres, te lo doy en formato:\n**“haz esto en 5 pasos”**  \nsin teoría, directo a configuración.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0fc121c358a0b3df0169c46fa37db0819185db8d393558391d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1068,"output":642,"cacheRead":14848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16558,"cost":{"input":0.00267,"output":0.00963,"cacheRead":0.003712,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.016012}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774481309419,"responseId":"resp_0fc121c358a0b3df0169c46fa1e10881918c0f0410155afbfc"}}
